				<p><p>I mentor several FTC (First Tech Challenge) Robotics Teams.  These teams build medium size robots (about 50cm cube starting size).</p>

<p>For this size, there are four Building Systems that are the most common</p>

<ol>
<li><a href="https://www.tetrixrobotics.com/" rel="nofollow noreferrer">Tetrix</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.modernroboticsinc.com/matrix" rel="nofollow noreferrer">Matrix</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.servocity.com/actobotics" rel="nofollow noreferrer">Actobotics</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.8020.net/" rel="nofollow noreferrer">8020 Extrusions</a> (There are lots of other suppliers too)</li>
</ol>

<p>These solutions are all very flexible allow a large about of options on how to build frames and attach motors, wheels, sensors, etc. and are designed for reuse.</p>

<p>Hotwired Robotics (one of our local FTC teams) wrote a great overview of the different <a href="http://hotwiredrobotics.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/HW-Robot-Build-Systems.pdf" rel="nofollow noreferrer">Building Systems</a>.</p>

<hr>

